interestingcomments.content: I can't understand this obsession as to where things are actually made. The items are what they are and either up to standard or they aren't. There seems to be a reliability problem with some of Leica's most expensive products that contributors on here are complaining about and returning that are made in Germany. There seems to be no evidence at all that the items are any better for having been made there. The geography is irrelevant, it's the skill of the people carrying out the assembly and the quality controls in place that's relevant, which quite clearly aren't that brilliant judging by complaints on here.
